description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a cancer wait time coordinator within the admin and clerical team in the Diagnostic Imaging Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant should be a highly motivated organised and forward thinking individual with excellent communication and team working skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Admin and clerical team provide key administrative functions within the busy Diagnostic Imaging service, including making appointments, reception duties and front-line interaction with service users as well as ensuring that the department meets the cancer wait targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cancer wait time coordinator needs to be able to learn quickly. You will need to be dynamic &amp; flexible with the ability to work accurately under pressure, to meet the changing service demands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit someone who will be a positive and who subscribes to the Trusts’ core values as they are at the heart of everything we do. Our values reflect the commitment we make to the people who use our services and to each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are one of only 5 Trusts in the country to be involved in the Virginia Mason Institute of excellence, a ground breaking scheme to transform patient care by developing streamlined processes and adding efficiencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 4th December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pauline Humphrey  Admin &amp; Clerical Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;paulinehumphrey@nhs.net  01737 768511 x 6011&lt;/p&gt;
